natural problem: If $\sqrt{3x-5}=2$, find all possible values of $x$.
natural solution: First, we start by squaring both sides of the equation \begin{align} (\sqrt{3x-5})^2& =(2)^2 \\ \Rightarrow\qquad 3x-5& =4 \\\Rightarrow\qquad 3x& =9 \\\Rightarrow\qquad x& =\boxed{3}. \end{align}Testing, we find that this value of $x$ does indeed satisfy the equation.
